<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../assets/xml/rss.xsl" media="all"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Brayden's Rants and Recipes (Posts by Sue Gallaher)</title><link>https://bstreete.github.io/</link><description></description><atom:link href="https://bstreete.github.io/authors/sue-gallaher.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><language>en</language><copyright>Contents © 2025 &lt;a href="mailto:bstreete@users.noreply.github.com"&gt;Brayden Streeter&lt;/a&gt; </copyright><lastBuildDate>Sun, 21 Dec 2025 15:10:10 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>Nikola (getnikola.com)</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>Baked Mac n' Cheese</title><link>https://bstreete.github.io/posts/recipes/mac-cheese-gallaher/</link><dc:creator>Sue Gallaher</dc:creator><description>&lt;div class="sect3"&gt;

&lt;h5 id="_variations"&gt;Variations&lt;/h5&gt;

&lt;div class="paragraph"&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can include chopped green chile, jalapenos, or bacon for an interesting spin on the classic.

## Ingredients&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="sect2"&gt;

&lt;h4 id="_casserole_ingredients"&gt;Casserole Ingredients&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;table class="tableblock frame-all grid-all stretch"&gt;

&lt;colgroup&gt;

&lt;col style="width: 50%;"&gt;

&lt;col style="width: 50%;"&gt;

&lt;/colgroup&gt;

&lt;tbody&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;4 cups hot, cooked elbow macaroni (roughly 1/2 pound uncooked)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;2 cups (8 oz) shredded sharp cheddar&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1 cup cottage cheese&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;3/4 cup sour cream&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1/2 cup skim milk&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;2 tablespoons grated onion&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1 1/2 teaspoon butter or margarine, melted&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1/2 teaspoon salt&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1/4 teaspoon pepper&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1 large egg, beaten&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/tbody&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="sect2"&gt;

&lt;h4 id="_topping_ingredients"&gt;Topping Ingredients&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;table class="tableblock frame-all grid-all stretch"&gt;

&lt;colgroup&gt;

&lt;col style="width: 50%;"&gt;

&lt;col style="width: 50%;"&gt;

&lt;/colgroup&gt;

&lt;tbody&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1/4 cup bread crumbs&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1 tablespoon butter or margarine&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1/4 teaspoon paprika&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/tbody&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="sect1"&gt;

&lt;h3 id="_directions"&gt;Directions&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;div class="sectionbody"&gt;

&lt;div class="olist arabic"&gt;

&lt;ol class="arabic"&gt;

&lt;li&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Preheat oven to 350°.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Combine the casserole ingredients together. Stir well. Spoon into a shallow 2 quart casserole dish coated with cooking spray.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Combine topping together, and sprinkle over the casserole.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cover and bake for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake for an additional 5 minutes or until breadcrumbs are slightly browned.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

